        "shortInsight": "In this code snippet we're trying to grab an element using document.getElementById with an ID of 12.",
        "teaching": "In this code snippet we're trying to grab an element using `document.getElementById` with an ID of `12`. However, TypeScript is complaining.\n\n```ts twoslash\n// @errors: 2345\nlet element = document.getElementById(12);\n```\n\nHow can hovering help to determine what argument `document.getElementById` actually requires? And for a bonus point, what type is `element`?\n\n<Exercise title=\"Exercise 1: Hovering a Function Call\" filePath=\"/src/016.5-ide-superpowers/041-hovering-a-function-call.problem.ts\"></Exercise>",
        "realLifeExample": "Here is a code example from the book:\n\n```ts\n// @errors: 2345\nlet element = document.getElementById(12);\n```",
        "quiz": {
            "question": "Choose the best answer to complete the sentence:\n\n\"______ TypeScript is complaining?\"",
            "options": [
                "Type Narrowing",
                "However",
                "Generics",
                "Conditional Types"
            ],
            "answer": "However"
        }
