        "teaching": "When working with object types in TypeScript, you'll often find yourself in situations where your object types share common properties. This can lead to a lot of duplicated code.\n\nWe've seen how using `interface extends` can help us model inheritance, but TypeScript also gives us tools to directly manipulate object types. With its built-in utility types, we can remove properties from types, make them optional, and more.",
