        "teaching": "The `ReturnType` utility type extracts the return type from a given function:\n\n```ts twoslash\ntype Album = {\n  title: string;\n  artist: string;\n  releaseYear: number;\n};\nfunction sellAlbum(album: Album, price: number, quantity: number) {\n  return price * quantity;\n}\n// ---cut---\ntype SellAlbumReturn = ReturnType<typeof sellAlbum>;\n//   ^?\n```\n\nIn this case, the `SellAlbumReturn` type is a number, which derived from the `sellAlbum` function.",
        "realLifeExample": "Here is a code example from the book:\n\n```ts\ntype Album = {\n  title: string;\n  artist: string;\n  releaseYear: number;\n};\nfunction sellAlbum(album: Album, price: number, quantity: number) {\n  return price * quantity;\n}\n// ---cut---\ntype SellAlbumReturn = ReturnType<typeof sellAlbum>;\n//   ^?\n```",
