        "shortInsight": "If we try to use variable annotation in the third example, we get the same error as with satisfies:    By process of elimination, as is the correct...",
        "teaching": "If we try to use variable annotation in the third example, we get the same error as with `satisfies`:\n\n```ts twoslash\n// @errors: 2322\nconst element: HTMLElement = document.getElementById(\"app\");\n```\n\nBy process of elimination, `as` is the correct choice for this scenario:\n\n```typescript\nconst element = document.getElementById(\"app\") as HTMLElement;\n```\n\nWith this change, `element` is inferred as `HTMLElement`.",
