        "shortInsight": "The key takeaway in this exercise is to grasp the mental model for when to use as, satisfies, and variable annotations:  Use as when you want to te...",
        "teaching": "The key takeaway in this exercise is to grasp the mental model for when to use `as`, `satisfies`, and variable annotations:\n\nUse `as` when you want to tell TypeScript that you know more than it does.\n\nUse `satisfies` when you want to make sure a value is checked without changing the inference on that value.\n\nThe rest of the time, use variable annotations.",
