        "topic": "Chapter 13: Modules Scripts Declaration Files",
        "subtopic": "Which DOM Types Get Included?",
        "shortInsight": "Different browsers support different features.",
        "teaching": "Different browsers support different features. A quick browse of [caniuse.com](https://caniuse.com/) will show how patchy browser support can be for certain features.\n\nBut TypeScript only ships one set of DOM types. So how does it know what to include?\n\nTypeScript's policy is that if a feature is supported in two major browsers, it's included in the DOM types. This is a good balance between including everything and including nothing.",
